249
00:21:53.860 --> 00:21:56.260
Right through those trees.

250
00:22:23.560 --> 00:22:27.090
No use cryin' over a lost shoe. boy

251
00:22:30.700 --> 00:22:33.170
The Children's Home... What happened to it?

252
00:22:33.570 --> 00:22:36.900
The German navy A bomb fell right on the roof.

253
00:22:37.500 --> 00:22:40.370
September the 3rd. 1943.

254
00:22:40.870 --> 00:22:42.580
Where... where did they go after it?

255
00:22:42.940 --> 00:22:44.940
The Headmistress and the children?

256
00:22:45.350 --> 00:22:47.510
Not one survivor.

257
00:22:47.920 --> 00:22:50.750
Poor little buggers... and they were lovely too.

258
00:22:52.390 --> 00:22:55.350
Why didn't he tell us that they all died?

259
00:22:55.920 --> 00:23:00.460
He leaves to join the army and three months everyone he knows gets killed?

260
00:23:01.090 --> 00:23:04.800
Not even grandpa can turn that into a bedtime story

261
00:23:05.270 --> 00:23:08.100
No wonder he was scared at being a dad.

262
00:23:08.500 --> 00:23:10.870
Being close to anyone.

263
00:23:11.810 --> 00:23:13.670
Listen.

264
00:23:14.240 --> 00:23:16.440
if you need to talk about all this with someone. buddy.

265
00:23:17.240 --> 00:23:19.680
We should call Dr. Golan.

266
00:23:27.850 --> 00:23:31.260
Do you mind if I go hang out with those other kids today?

267
00:23:32.390 --> 00:23:33.690
They asked.

268
00:23:34.090 --> 00:23:35.800
Yeah. That's awesome

269
00:25:10.260 --> 00:25:11.920
Abe?

270
00:26:00.670 --> 00:26:02.170
You're Emma

271
00:26:02.810 --> 00:26:04.510
And the twins.

272
00:26:05.050 --> 00:26:06.450
And Olive

273
00:26:06.850 --> 00:26:08.480
Bromwin

274
00:26:09.320 --> 00:26:10.920
He's Miller.

275
00:26:11.690 --> 00:26:12.990
You are dead

276
00:26:13.290 --> 00:26:14.990
All of you. You're all dead

277
00:26:15.620 --> 00:26:18.060
I mean he is...he is invisible he's still dead

278
00:26:18.530 --> 00:26:20.860
None of us are dead

279
00:26:21.530 --> 00:26:22.930
[Oh my God] Am I dead?

280
00:26:23.500 --> 00:26:24.730
No

281
00:26:27.030 --> 00:26:30.500
You called me Abe. in the house. Why?

282
00:26:31.100 --> 00:26:32.670
You look like him.

283
00:26:33.070 --> 00:26:34.370
Just for a moment

284
00:26:34.780 --> 00:26:38.210
Before you started screaming. running away and concussing yourself.

285
00:26:38.650 --> 00:26:40.150
Wait. what's happening?

286
00:26:40.580 --> 00:26:43.680
We are waiting until the coast is clear before we go into the loop.

287
00:26:44.350 --> 00:26:46.750
You never know who might be watching.

288
00:26:47.320 --> 00:26:49.660
Wait. before we...before we go into what?

289
00:26:50.020 --> 00:26:55.630
Please Jake Ms. peregrine's waiting. She saw on the ferry and sent us to get you.

290
00:27:46.780 --> 00:27:48.610
Where do you think you're going?

291
00:27:49.420 --> 00:27:51.150
To my room

292
00:27:52.750 --> 00:27:54.420
Im a...I am a guest here

293
00:27:55.020 --> 00:27:58.060
Does this look like a hotel to you?

294
00:27:59.730 --> 00:28:01.630
Yeah...No!.

295
00:28:02.560 --> 00:28:04.230
I've....I've got a key.

296
00:28:04.360 --> 00:28:06.970
Talk to the manager. He'll tell you.

297
00:28:07.530 --> 00:28:09.200
I'm the manager. boy.

298
00:28:09.540 --> 00:28:10.600
He's American.

299
00:28:10.940 --> 00:28:12.270
Maybe he's army?

300
00:28:12.570 --> 00:28:15.780
Bollocks! Listen to his accent. It's terrible!

301
00:28:16.780 --> 00:28:18.540
He is a spy.

302
00:28:19.480 --> 00:28:20.580
What?

303
00:28:20.980 --> 00:28:23.280
No. I'm not I'm a tourist

304
00:28:23.980 --> 00:28:27.790
I say. we should get the truth out of him - the old-fashioned way.

305
00:29:01.560 --> 00:29:04.120
Come on. quick guys.

306
00:29:14.130 --> 00:29:15.870
I can't believe you're real.

307
00:29:16.270 --> 00:29:17.270
You're all real

308
00:29:17.600 --> 00:29:18.916
We've been trying to tell you.

309
00:29:18.940 --> 00:29:20.060
But I am special too.

310
00:29:20.210 --> 00:29:21.210
What?

311
00:29:21.480 --> 00:29:23.110
In the pub all of you saw it. Right?

312
00:29:23.480 --> 00:29:27.350
Everything was flying and breaking. And that was me.

313
00:29:27.710 --> 00:29:29.650
I was doing it with my mind.

314
00:29:30.020 --> 00:29:31.950
No. that was me

315
00:29:32.790 --> 00:29:34.120
Miller? Yeah.

316
00:29:36.760 --> 00:29:38.420
Are you naked? Yeah

317
00:29:45.830 --> 00:29:48.430
A bomb drops on you in 1943.

318
00:29:48.800 --> 00:29:50.440
It is 1943

319
00:29:50.870 --> 00:29:53.370
September the 3rd. 1943

320
00:29:53.770 --> 00:29:55.510
The whole day. every day

321
00:29:55.780 --> 00:29:57.440
Its our loop

322
00:30:29.040 --> 00:30:31.340
Right on time

323
00:30:32.010 --> 00:30:34.410
Ms. Peregrine. Delighted to meet you.

324
00:30:35.020 --> 00:30:38.380
I do hope Im not going to have the pub landlord knocking
on my door with the police again?

325
00:30:38.790 --> 00:30:40.850
I've had to kill them twice this month

326
00:30:41.150 --> 00:30:42.720
Its been terribly inconvenient.

327
00:30:43.060 --> 00:30:45.020
We may have broken some things. that's all.

328
00:30:45.730 --> 00:30:49.100
And Olive may have started a tiny fire

329
00:30:49.900 --> 00:30:52.400
But they were going to hurt Jake.

330
00:30:55.840 --> 00:30:57.340
Look at you!

331
00:30:58.040 --> 00:31:01.910
The last time dear Abe sent me a photograph.
you were a just a tiny todd.

332
00:31:02.380 --> 00:31:03.610
Don't you stand there. come in.

333
00:31:03.980 --> 00:31:05.810
Your tea is getting cold.

334
00:31:07.610 --> 00:31:09.680
How did you know about the pub?

335
00:31:10.180 --> 00:31:12.320
Your weigh approximately a 109 pounds. correct?

336
00:31:12.890 --> 00:31:15.450
Bronwyn and the twins returned six minutes after you ran away.

337
00:31:15.760 --> 00:31:16.890
I think Im missing something.

338
00:31:17.060 --> 00:31:20.390
And quite apart from the fact that the perceived safety of the pub
makes it...

339
00:31:20.730 --> 00:31:22.360
the most likely place to which you would flee?

340
00:31:22.660 --> 00:31:24.260
It would take you 18 minutes to run there.

341
00:31:24.530 --> 00:31:28.300
Emma and Miller would have been moments behind with the
horse and trap travelling at around 8.2 miles per hour.

342
00:31:28.740 --> 00:31:33.010
Fact doing some sort of Kerfuffle in the pub and
the return journey with your added weight.

343
00:31:33.510 --> 00:31:36.480
You would arrive here with 30 minutes past 4

344
00:31:36.980 --> 00:31:38.980
now then. do you like sugar?

345
00:31:40.180 --> 00:31:43.820
That will be enough. thank you Olive. Nobody enjoys overboiled tea.

346
00:31:54.060 --> 00:31:56.300
Let me help you. Enoch.

347
00:31:56.600 --> 00:31:57.830
Do not bother.

348
00:31:58.230 --> 00:32:00.900
Wouldn't want you to interrupt the tea party.

349
00:32:09.080 --> 00:32:11.410
I'm so sorry for your loss. Jake.

350
00:32:12.850 --> 00:32:14.810
You know. then?

351
00:32:16.050 --> 00:32:17.720
I know if Abe were alive

352
00:32:18.050 --> 00:32:20.420
You would have told me you were coming.

353
00:32:22.760 --> 00:32:25.390
Shall we take our tea outside?

354
00:32:29.300 --> 00:32:32.200
Before he died he told me to find you.

355
00:32:32.570 --> 00:32:35.100
There was something he wanted me to know

356
00:32:35.400 --> 00:32:37.040
He said you could explain everything.

357
00:32:37.340 --> 00:32:40.910
That's absolutely true. But there are few things I can't explain

358
00:32:41.240 --> 00:32:45.240
We are in common parlance - as peculiar

359
00:32:47.310 --> 00:32:49.320
51 seconds late. Fiona.

360
00:32:49.680 --> 00:32:50.950
Sorry Ms. Peregrine

361
00:32:51.250 --> 00:32:52.850
How many carrots you need for supper?

362
00:32:53.120 --> 00:32:54.920
Just one will do.

363
00:33:09.070 --> 00:33:12.670
As I was saying some people are peculiar

364
00:33:13.070 --> 00:33:15.610
Its a recessive gene carried down through families.

365
00:33:16.240 --> 00:33:20.580
Yet. many generations can pass without a peculiar child being born

366
00:33:20.950 --> 00:33:25.020
And alas. peculiars have been persecuted through the ages

367
00:33:25.420 --> 00:33:27.950
Hence. we live in places like this.

368
00:33:28.820 --> 00:33:30.020
in Wales?

369
00:33:30.390 --> 00:33:32.366
Anywhere will do if you pick the right day.

370
00:33:32.390 --> 00:33:35.230
Thats fine now. Fiona.

371
00:33:38.600 --> 00:33:42.540
You see. I am a type of peculiar called an Ymbryne. That means I can....

372
00:33:43.040 --> 00:33:44.600
You can turn into a bird.

373
00:33:44.810 --> 00:33:47.840
Well I do! But that's not very useful.

374
00:33:48.380 --> 00:33:51.340
An Ymbryne's main skill is the manipulation of time.

375
00:33:51.680 --> 00:33:56.220
We chose a safe place. a safe day and create a loop

376
00:33:56.480 --> 00:33:57.820
What do you mean?

377
00:33:58.250 --> 00:34:01.390
A loop preserves the last 24 hours.

378
00:34:01.720 --> 00:34:04.860
Reset the loop and the day is yours to live in again.

379
00:34:05.190 --> 00:34:08.190
Reset it daily and you can stay there forever

380
00:34:08.630 --> 00:34:11.360
Entirely safe from the outside world

381
00:34:11.830 --> 00:34:14.630
Right on time Bronwyn. good girl

382
00:34:19.010 --> 00:34:23.510
And thats why we Ymbrynes are charged with the care of the young.

383
00:34:25.910 --> 00:34:28.350
And no one ever gets older?

384
00:34:28.720 --> 00:34:30.920
Its best for everyone this way

385
00:34:31.520 --> 00:34:32.920
I assure you.

386
00:34:35.860 --> 00:34:40.590
Each Ymbryne commits herself to the creation and upkeep
of a place like this

387
00:34:41.030 --> 00:34:43.960
A Home for Peculiar Children.

388
00:34:56.440 --> 00:34:58.440
You've met the twins

389
00:35:03.550 --> 00:35:05.180
This is Claire

390
00:35:16.960 --> 00:35:18.930
Miller you've met

391
00:35:21.130 --> 00:35:24.070
And that's Hugh

392
00:35:26.770 --> 00:35:29.380
Stop cheating Hugh

393
00:35:29.940 --> 00:35:31.980
Miller thats a foul. again!

394
00:35:32.610 --> 00:35:33.910
No it wasn't!

395
00:35:35.420 --> 00:35:39.050
If you two cant play without squabbling.
wish you wouldn't play at all.

396
00:35:39.490 --> 00:35:41.220
Look who our referee is.

397
00:35:41.860 --> 00:35:45.220
Good afternoon. I'm Horace. Delighted to meet you

398
00:35:47.030 --> 00:35:48.630
We sorely needed some new blood here.

399
00:35:49.460 --> 00:35:52.030
Super shirt by the way

400
00:35:52.500 --> 00:35:53.800
Thanks

401
00:35:57.700 --> 00:36:00.040
You know Emma. of course

402
00:36:00.810 --> 00:36:02.610
And I think thats everyone.

403
00:36:03.380 --> 00:36:05.510
Didn't Bronwyn have a brother?

404
00:36:06.080 --> 00:36:08.210
Yes. Victor's upstairs.

405
00:36:08.850 --> 00:36:10.620
Wait. where did Enoch and Olive go?

406
00:36:12.950 --> 00:36:13.980
Heaven knows.

407
00:36:14.290 --> 00:36:16.450
Enoch's been off ever since we went to look for Jake.

408
00:36:16.860 --> 00:36:19.890
Ms. Peregrine there's a policemen at the door.
He says it's about the pub.

409
00:36:21.390 --> 00:36:25.500
We discuss this later. Emma.

410
00:36:25.900 --> 00:36:27.930
It wasn't their fault

411
00:36:28.530 --> 00:36:31.570
Honestly. just they were just trying to help

412
00:36:40.850 --> 00:36:44.050
Thanks. You're not as vet as I thought

413
00:36:47.390 --> 00:36:50.350
She's not really going to kill anyone. is she?

414
00:36:50.720 --> 00:36:52.820
Not if she can talk her way out of it.

415
00:36:53.220 --> 00:36:54.660
Would you help me with something.

416
00:36:55.130 --> 00:36:58.200
Enoch usually does it but. like I said. he is sulking somewhere.

417
00:36:59.060 --> 00:37:00.760
Is that because of me?

418
00:37:01.200 --> 00:37:03.300
He is possessive

419
00:37:05.600 --> 00:37:08.370
So.... What you need help with?

420
00:37:08.840 --> 00:37:10.070
One of my daily chores.

421
00:37:10.480 --> 00:37:12.640
Put the baby squirrel back in the tree.

422
00:37:12.940 --> 00:37:15.150
What baby squirrel?

423
00:37:19.680 --> 00:37:21.290
That happens every day?

424
00:37:21.590 --> 00:37:23.320
Like clockwork.

425
00:37:24.390 --> 00:37:26.920
Now. would you mind tying that rope around my waist?

426
00:37:28.530 --> 00:37:29.530
Uh...Yeah.

427
00:37:56.890 --> 00:37:59.360
Right. Promise to hold on tight?

428
00:38:44.240 --> 00:38:46.570
I knew we messed that up.

429
00:38:46.640 --> 00:38:49.240
Abe did too... the first time.

430
00:38:49.840 --> 00:38:52.210
This used to be his job

431
00:38:53.910 --> 00:38:56.650
Emma. ​​I need to tell you something.

432
00:38:58.020 --> 00:39:00.080
He is dead.

433
00:39:00.890 --> 00:39:04.560
I know. Ms. Peregrine guessed and she's always right.

434
00:39:06.120 --> 00:39:07.360
It's okay

435
00:39:08.130 --> 00:39:10.890
I said goodbye to him a long time ago

436
00:39:11.330 --> 00:39:13.600
Were you close?

437
00:39:14.770 --> 00:39:16.770
I thought we were.

438
00:39:17.470 --> 00:39:19.170
For a while.

439
00:39:19.640 --> 00:39:21.840
But I suppose not

440
00:39:23.580 --> 00:39:27.210
Can I ask. was he like you?

441
00:39:29.480 --> 00:39:32.320
He was like you. Jake.

442
00:39:34.020 --> 00:39:35.690
I need to go change for supper.

443
00:39:35.990 --> 00:39:37.590
Will you be dining with us?

444
00:39:37.920 --> 00:39:39.290
I can't stay out late.

445
00:39:39.620 --> 00:39:41.630
Suppers at 5:30

446
00:39:42.890 --> 00:39:45.130
Well that's pretty early

447
00:39:45.600 --> 00:39:48.500
The fact we are not all eight years of olds seems
to have eluded Ms. Peregrine

448
00:39:49.330 --> 00:39:53.170
You can borrow some of Abe's clothes. His room's in the attic

449
00:40:03.820 --> 00:40:05.150
Jake

450
00:40:05.520 --> 00:40:07.950
Come meet Enoch. properly.

451
00:40:17.730 --> 00:40:20.800
Well. you must feel pretty out of place.

452
00:40:21.770 --> 00:40:24.800
Don't worry. I am used to it.

453
00:40:25.240 --> 00:40:27.910
I wasn't worried. Some advice for you though.

454
00:40:28.370 --> 00:40:29.810
Man to man

455
00:40:30.210 --> 00:40:32.640
If you think you're staying just because you like Emma.

456
00:40:32.980 --> 00:40:34.110
Don't bother

457
00:40:34.510 --> 00:40:38.180
You see she swore off romance years ago when
she got her heart broken

458
00:40:38.650 --> 00:40:41.190
And she's never gonna change her mind.

459
00:40:44.420 --> 00:40:46.890
Enoch. I wasn't....

460
00:40:48.030 --> 00:40:50.090
What are you doing?

461
00:41:19.660 --> 00:41:21.360
Isn't he amazing?

462
00:41:21.730 --> 00:41:23.290
What did you do?

463
00:41:23.700 --> 00:41:25.060
This?

464
00:41:25.630 --> 00:41:27.770
Jake. This is not even the fun part.

465
00:41:28.170 --> 00:41:30.330
Do you want to see the fun part?

466
00:41:53.860 --> 00:41:55.660
They are like puppets.

467
00:41:56.700 --> 00:41:59.700
Just do anything I tell them.

468
00:42:00.600 --> 00:42:02.170
It is even more fun with people

469
00:42:02.900 --> 00:42:05.140
You should have seen some of the epic battles I used to have

470
00:42:05.300 --> 00:42:07.870
Emma ***********

471
00:42:09.670 --> 00:42:12.880
You need a necktie.

472
00:42:19.580 --> 00:42:23.120
So. What did my grandpa do when he was traveling?

473
00:42:23.660 --> 00:42:25.490
Visited other loops.

474
00:42:25.920 --> 00:42:27.260
Really?

475
00:42:27.630 --> 00:42:28.990
To do what?

476
00:42:29.530 --> 00:42:32.730
Jake. there are some questions I can't answer. alright?

477
00:42:33.330 --> 00:42:38.070
So it will be a lot easier for me if you just
stopped asking them.

478
00:42:56.890 --> 00:42:58.460
Hey. what are you doing?

479
00:42:59.060 --> 00:43:01.090
Miller. go and put some clothes on.

480
00:43:01.690 --> 00:43:03.930
Polite persons do not take the sup in the nude!

481
00:43:04.300 --> 00:43:06.160
Alright!

482
00:43:08.700 --> 00:43:11.340
You can sit here Jake.

483
00:43:13.000 --> 00:43:15.810
Look at Enoch. He's jealous.

484
00:43:16.310 --> 00:43:18.040
Why would I be jealous?

485
00:43:18.510 --> 00:43:20.280
All of you can go marry Jake for all I care.

486
00:43:20.710 --> 00:43:24.750
Do not be mean. Enoch. She doesn't want to.
She's just excited to a visitor.

487
00:43:25.180 --> 00:43:26.880
Nobody is marrying anybody.

488
00:43:27.290 --> 00:43:30.590
Now eat up your food before it gets cold.

489
00:43:33.490 --> 00:43:35.030
Hugh

490
00:43:36.090 --> 00:43:38.060
Where's your net?

491
00:43:51.010 --> 00:43:52.840
It must be very strange for you Jake.

492
00:43:53.450 --> 00:43:55.310
To meet your grandfather's friends.

493
00:43:55.780 --> 00:43:57.250
Visiting another century.

494
00:43:57.650 --> 00:43:59.250
There spaceships in your time. Jake.

495
00:43:59.380 --> 00:44:00.820
Like the Flash Gordon books?

496
00:44:01.290 --> 00:44:04.320
Now! Now! Olive. what did I say about the questions.

497
00:44:04.790 --> 00:44:06.190
We don't discuss the future here.

498
00:44:06.560 --> 00:44:09.560
We enjoy living in the here and now

499
00:44:11.800 --> 00:44:13.960
Claire. why aren't you eating?

500
00:44:14.370 --> 00:44:16.130
She's embarassed in front of Jake.

501
00:44:16.430 --> 00:44:19.000
Don't be. please.

502
00:44:35.990 --> 00:44:38.090
So. Jake. what is your peculiarity?

503
00:44:38.820 --> 00:44:41.130
Oh. I'm... I'm not peculiar.

504
00:44:41.660 --> 00:44:44.060
And that my friends is why he'll not be staying with us.

505
00:44:44.500 --> 00:44:46.800
No matter how hard we try to persuade him.

506
00:44:47.170 --> 00:44:49.600
We've spoken about this. Jake is just visiting.

507
00:44:49.970 --> 00:44:52.670
Do you not want to stay. Jake?

508
00:44:53.040 --> 00:44:54.370
Tonight or ..

509
00:44:54.670 --> 00:44:56.710
Forever. You should stay forever.

510
00:44:57.110 --> 00:44:59.410
Why would he if he doesn't have to?

511
00:44:59.740 --> 00:45:03.250
He can live out there. Grow older and have a good time instead.

512
00:45:03.650 --> 00:45:06.280
And leave. Just like his grandfather did.

513
00:45:11.160 --> 00:45:12.290
Emma!

514
00:45:12.590 --> 00:45:14.630
Excuse me. where she's going?

515
00:45:14.990 --> 00:45:16.330
That wasn't nice. Enoch!

516
00:45:16.630 --> 00:45:18.430
You know perfectly well why Abe left us.

517
00:45:18.760 --> 00:45:19.960
To join the army.

518
00:45:20.330 --> 00:45:24.230
And then he met a lady. And had a nice wedding cake.And a lovely little baby.

519
00:45:24.700 --> 00:45:26.500
Children!

520
00:45:27.510 --> 00:45:29.610
I know you'd all like a new friend

521
00:45:29.980 --> 00:45:32.840
But I'm sure Jake has plenty of his own back in  Florida.

522
00:45:36.250 --> 00:45:39.950
I think you should all get ready for movie-time while I answer that

523
00:45:40.590 --> 00:45:43.390
But you always let us stay for it.

524
00:46:01.240 --> 00:46:03.510
Hi. this is Abe.

525
00:46:03.980 --> 00:46:06.410
How is everyone?

526
00:46:12.280 --> 00:46:13.980
Yours has extra marshmallows. Jake.

527
00:46:14.450 --> 00:46:16.520
Miller. put some pajamas on.

528
00:46:16.790 --> 00:46:18.120
It is very hot in here

529
00:46:18.460 --> 00:46:20.920
Stop moaning.
Excuse me.

530
00:46:29.370 --> 00:46:31.300
My grandpa told me about this.

531
00:46:31.840 --> 00:46:33.700
Horace projects his dreams. right?

532
00:46:34.140 --> 00:46:35.810
He used to listen to the radio.

533
00:46:36.370 --> 00:46:38.880
Gets tedious when you know every word off by heart.

534
00:46:42.050 --> 00:46:44.050
Splendid. I'll take it.

535
00:46:44.480 --> 00:46:46.150
It sounds about clothes mostly.

536
00:46:46.480 --> 00:46:48.190
Delighted to meet you

537
00:46:48.790 --> 00:46:50.990
Super shirt by the way.

538
00:46:53.220 --> 00:46:55.290
When did he dream this?

539
00:46:55.560 --> 00:46:56.760
Last night

540
00:46:57.100 --> 00:46:58.860
Some of his dreams are prophetic

541
00:46:59.230 --> 00:47:01.870
But mostly they are about clothes.

542
00:47:02.230 --> 00:47:05.800
Prophetic as in. he can see into the future?

543
00:47:19.680 --> 00:47:23.450
The Ymbryne. Who is she? Mrs. Peregrine. you know her?

544
00:47:23.920 --> 00:47:26.990
Don't be silly. Horace was just having a bad dream. Thats all

545
00:48:01.160 --> 00:48:03.890
Thats quite enough. Thank you Horace.

546
00:48:04.430 --> 00:48:06.300
I think probably get going

547
00:48:06.670 --> 00:48:10.900
You could stay the night. If you wanted to.
Rather than walk home in the dark.

548
00:48:11.570 --> 00:48:14.100
But the island is very safe. isn't it?

549
00:48:14.470 --> 00:48:15.770
Of course

550
00:48:16.340 --> 00:48:18.540
I only meant the path is dreadfully bumpy.
Jake could trip.

551
00:48:19.110 --> 00:48:24.720
Perhaps you could show him the shortcuts?
Should he ever need to avoid...bumps.

552
00:48:25.220 --> 00:48:28.790
Wont you stay to see the restart. It is really quite spectacular.

553
00:51:12.220 --> 00:51:13.380
What was that?

554
00:51:13.790 --> 00:51:15.390
It was my phone.

555
00:51:16.050 --> 00:51:18.370
It's been dead the whole time in the loop I guess now ...

556
00:51:18.660 --> 00:51:20.260
Your phone?

557
00:51:20.630 --> 00:51:25.330
Yeah. ****** like a telephone? You can call people...

558
00:51:25.760 --> 00:51:29.170
And send written messages.

559
00:51:29.970 --> 00:51:31.740
Right. You'll love this. You can take a picture.

560
00:51:32.140 --> 00:51:34.310
Press that... there...yeah.

561
00:51:35.070 --> 00:51:36.670
See?

562
00:51:43.620 --> 00:51:45.620
Whats wrong?

563
00:51:48.420 --> 00:51:53.290
Its just funny to think that one day you'll grow up
like Abe did.

564
00:51:53.690 --> 00:51:55.860
Get married... have children.

565
00:51:56.290 --> 00:51:57.960
Grandchildren

566
00:51:58.360 --> 00:52:01.400
You might even******* photograph.

567
00:52:01.830 --> 00:52:04.470
And I'll still be here.

568
00:52:05.070 --> 00:52:07.200
Wha... can you leave some day?

569
00:52:07.670 --> 00:52:09.970
And live in the present if you wanted to?

570
00:52:10.280 --> 00:52:15.910
No. More than a few minutes in your time
and the years would catch up

571
00:52:16.380 --> 00:52:18.620
You'd age?

572
00:52:19.150 --> 00:52:20.420
Would... you're...

573
00:52:26.320 --> 00:52:28.560
I think it is the Ymbryne from Horace's dream.

574
00:52:29.230 --> 00:52:31.630
Are you sure it's not just a bird?

575
00:52:32.060 --> 00:52:33.730
I mean. I don't know... wouldn't it change?

576
00:52:34.070 --> 00:52:36.770
She can't. Not if she's hurt.

577
00:52:37.100 --> 00:52:40.570
I need to take her inside. You should go.

578
00:52:42.670 --> 00:52:46.210
Please do not say anything else. I hate goodbyes

579
00:52:48.810 --> 00:52:50.910
I'll come back tomorrow

580
00:52:51.220 --> 00:52:54.890
There's no hurry. I'll be here forever.

581
00:53:02.060 --> 00:53:03.190
Hey.

582
00:53:04.800 --> 00:53:07.330
Have I been all this damn island Where the hell were you?

583
00:53:07.830 --> 00:53:09.800
I was just on my way back.

584
00:53:10.170 --> 00:53:12.200
Sorry. I lost track of time.

585
00:53:12.340 --> 00:53:14.070
I was having a blast with Worm....

586
00:53:14.610 --> 00:53:15.810
and Dirty D?

587
00:53:16.110 --> 00:53:17.840
Dirty D?

588
00:53:18.540 --> 00:53:20.740
You know what? This is... this is good

589
00:53:21.050 --> 00:53:24.280
This is healthy. This is you're making real friends

590
00:53:24.880 --> 00:53:27.020
Doing teenage stuff.

591
00:53:27.350 --> 00:53:29.826
I think this is normal. I am sure that Dr. Golan will approve.

592
00:53:29.850 --> 00:53:31.160
Hey. you American

593
00:53:31.460 --> 00:53:33.220
Get over here

594
00:53:34.630 --> 00:53:38.800
Hey look here there they are. theres D-bag and worm-man

595
00:53:39.160 --> 00:53:40.830
Did you do this?

596
00:53:41.330 --> 00:53:43.900
What? No!

597
00:53:44.500 --> 00:53:45.840
Of course not

598
00:53:46.200 --> 00:53:47.670
It wasn't us.

599
00:53:48.270 --> 00:53:50.910
Listen Sir. I don't know what happened here but my son
and his friends

600
00:53:51.240 --> 00:53:54.680
Have been together all day.
And Jake would never do anything like this.

601
00:53:54.980 --> 00:53:56.780
Bollocks! We haven't seen him!

602
00:53:57.080 --> 00:54:00.580
You paid us yesterday.
Why would we hang out with him today for free?

603
00:54:02.450 --> 00:54:05.320
Jake were you with them or not?

604
00:54:06.660 --> 00:54:09.390
No! I'm sorry!

605
00:54:10.100 --> 00:54:13.000
And you don't seriously think I could do this?

606
00:54:13.500 --> 00:54:16.000
I think we're done here. sir.

607
00:54:16.530 --> 00:54:18.570
Well. can pass on a message for me?

608
00:54:19.040 --> 00:54:23.040
Can you tell Dr. Golan that if she hadn't encouraged this cockamamie trip

609
00:54:23.340 --> 00:54:28.850
maybe my son wouldn't be mopping around all day in a derelict house
HAVING A GODDAMN BREAKDOWN.

610
00:54:29.280 --> 00:54:30.280
Hello?

611
00:54:30.420 --> 00:54:32.650
Dad. I'm not.

612
00:54:32.950 --> 00:54:34.080
I'm fine

613
00:54:34.520 --> 00:54:36.250
You're not.

614
00:54:36.720 --> 00:54:39.120
You are not fine. Jake.

615
00:54:39.720 --> 00:54:42.890
Coming here was a terrible... terrible idea.

616
00:54:43.230 --> 00:54:44.800
Im sorry. I lied ..

617
00:54:45.700 --> 00:54:47.970
Set your alarm for 8:00 am.

618
00:54:48.570 --> 00:54:50.230
I want to get to the beach early.

619
00:54:50.570 --> 00:54:54.640
The rest of the time left on this crap-o-island.
we're stickin together.

620
00:54:55.410 --> 00:54:56.770
Where are you going?

621
00:54:57.110 --> 00:54:59.180
Downstairs for a drink.

622
00:55:47.490 --> 00:55:50.630
Dearest Peregrine: I don't wish to alarm you...

623
00:55:51.030 --> 00:55:53.930
but one of my informants sent me this.

624
00:55:54.470 --> 00:55:59.140
It would appear that some of Mr. Barron's group were in Black Pool. England.

625
00:55:59.940 --> 00:56:04.140
If I recall. Ms. Avocet has a loop there. "

626
00:56:04.680 --> 00:56:08.550
Please warn her and suggest that she make a new one right away. "

627
00:56:08.910 --> 00:56:10.110
Well hidden. "

628
00:56:10.420 --> 00:56:17.520
And take the greatest care yourself. With Love. Abe. January 2016

629
00:56:35.170 --> 00:56:38.240
Who is ready to hit the beach?

630
00:56:43.380 --> 00:56:45.550
Oh my goodness

631
00:56:46.080 --> 00:56:47.620
Unbelievable!

632
00:56:48.350 --> 00:56:50.450
Im right in the middle of a nesting are?

633
00:56:50.890 --> 00:56:53.020
What kind of idiot does that?

634
00:56:54.160 --> 00:56:57.490
Actually. the main nesting area is over there.

635
00:56:57.960 --> 00:56:59.360
I can show you. if you like.

636
00:56:59.700 --> 00:57:01.940
It's marvellous to meet a fellow bird-spotter!

637
00:57:02.170 --> 00:57:03.730
John Lamont.
Franklyn Portman.

638
00:57:04.100 --> 00:57:05.400
This is my son. Jake.

639
00:57:05.740 --> 00:57:07.270
John Newmont.

640
00:57:07.610 --> 00:57:09.440
That's a hell of a camera you got there.

641
00:57:09.870 --> 00:57:12.110
Oh. thank you. is absolutely fantastic.

642
00:57:12.580 --> 00:57:15.020
I am here to do some snaps for a book I'm writing.

643
00:57:15.350 --> 00:57:18.950
So. you gentlemen are here on holiday?

644
00:57:28.890 --> 00:57:31.160
So. you are not coming to the beach today?

645
00:57:31.500 --> 00:57:32.760
What's the point?

646
00:57:33.130 --> 00:57:38.240
That guys gonna cover ****** on some big glossy book.
no ones even wanna look at mine.

647
00:57:39.270 --> 00:57:42.040
I might just have a nice afternoon nap.

648
00:57:42.670 --> 00:57:45.190
I do not suppose you saw uncle Oggie on you travels this morning.
did you?

649
00:57:45.540 --> 00:57:47.510
He's usually here by now.

650
00:57:47.850 --> 00:57:49.150
I could go look for him.

651
00:57:49.450 --> 00:57:51.580
You're not going anywhere

652
00:58:27.480 --> 00:58:30.950
Jake. you're back! Come and play!

653
00:58:34.290 --> 00:58:36.460
I need to see to Ms. Peregrine first.

654
00:58:36.830 --> 00:58:38.700
Do you know where she is?

655
00:58:43.100 --> 00:58:45.900
Jake. you're back. How wonderful!

656
00:58:46.440 --> 00:58:48.000
How's it doing?

657
00:58:48.510 --> 00:58:50.270
Emma said it was an Ymbryne.

658
00:58:50.640 --> 00:58:53.780
She. not 'it'. Ymbrynes are always female.

659
00:58:54.140 --> 00:58:56.850
And Emma was quite correct. This is Ms. Avocet

660
00:58:57.280 --> 00:59:00.380
Her loop is in Black Pool England.

661
00:59:02.490 --> 00:59:04.920
That was a private letter. Jake.

662
00:59:07.460 --> 00:59:10.090
Who is Mr Barron?

663
00:59:11.260 --> 00:59:15.160
Ms. Peregrine. if my grandpa was involved with dangerous people

664
00:59:15.570 --> 00:59:17.870
I need to tell the police.

665
00:59:18.240 --> 00:59:20.000
To the police?

666
00:59:20.500 --> 00:59:23.340
Are you implying Abe died an unnatural death?

667
00:59:23.710 --> 00:59:26.640
I found him in the woods with eyes missing.

668
00:59:27.310 --> 00:59:30.580
I'd say that was pretty unnatural.

669
00:59:33.980 --> 00:59:37.150
Unless essential. I don't
discuss unpleasant matters.

670
00:59:37.620 --> 00:59:40.390
An Ymbryne's is a duty to
protect children. Jake.

671
00:59:40.990 --> 00:59:43.060
I am not a child

672
00:59:43.730 --> 00:59:46.430
He wanted you to tell me everything.

673
00:59:50.700 --> 00:59:53.340
Oh. How frustrating for you.

674
00:59:53.900 --> 00:59:57.340
Between Ms. Peregrine rules and
my ******* not to scare you off

675
00:59:57.840 --> 00:59:59.940
It's like no ones telling you anything?!

676
01:00:00.510 --> 01:00:02.680
So why don't you then?

677
01:00:03.010 --> 01:00:04.850
It's not like you want me here

678
01:00:05.150 --> 01:00:06.280
Enoch. you can't

679
01:00:06.550 --> 01:00:08.120
You promised

680
01:00:08.450 --> 01:00:09.890
Olive is right

681
01:00:10.290 --> 01:00:13.260
However. I know someone
who can break the rules.

682
01:00:13.660 --> 01:00:15.960
Want to meet him?

683
01:00:15.990 --> 01:00:18.760
Enoch. do not do this! Please

684
01:00:19.300 --> 01:00:22.730
You didn't want us to spend time together.
That's what you said.

685
01:00:24.740 --> 01:00:27.040
Well. here we all are.

686
01:00:27.500 --> 01:00:29.310
Move. Olive

687
01:00:29.710 --> 01:00:33.380
If you're going to be like then I
do not want to be your friend.

688
01:00:35.710 --> 01:00:39.750
Enoch! Leave Victor alone. It really upsets Bromwyn.

689
01:00:40.250 --> 01:00:43.350
Stop fussing. Fiona. Don't you think Jake should meet everybody?

690
01:00:43.650 --> 01:00:45.266
He's trying to frighten you away. Jake.

691
01:00:45.290 --> 01:00:47.690
He was always jealous of Abe and now he's jealous of you.

692
01:00:47.860 --> 01:00:50.630
Come and play with us instead

693
01:00:54.030 --> 01:00:57.070
I'd quite like to meet Victor

694
01:01:02.770 --> 01:01:04.710
After You.

695
01:01:12.820 --> 01:01:14.480
Hello Victor.

696
01:01:14.950 --> 01:01:18.890
I'm Jake. Im sorry to disturb....

697
01:01:21.930 --> 01:01:23.430
He can't hear you

698
01:01:48.590 --> 01:01:53.160
Hello Jake. I'm Victor. Do you want to know what killed me?

699
01:02:00.030 --> 01:02:03.770
Ah. there you are. ****** Its time for our daily walk.

700
01:02:06.670 --> 01:02:11.039
Emma. Who killed Victor? Was it the people with the white eyes?

701
01:02:11.040 --> 01:02:15.140
I asked you not to ask questions.
I saw one the night my grandpa died.

702
01:02:18.920 --> 01:02:24.049
If it really was one. you have to tell Ms. Peregrinee.
Could you recognize you recognize him from a photograph?

703
01:02:24.050 --> 01:02:30.060
Do you have one? Then come on. Theres somewhere I go to be alone.
I have things there.

704
01:03:07.600 --> 01:03:11.030
Is this the place?
No. This is how we get there.

705
01:03:30.720 --> 01:03:34.290
Emma! Your shoes! Lead shoes!

706
01:05:36.080 --> 01:05:41.180
Welcome to my secret hideout.
How? How did you...

707
01:05:41.850 --> 01:05:47.560
Air. My peculiarity. It does what I want

708
01:06:06.880 --> 01:06:12.120
Jake. Before your grandfather retired.
he asked me to keep this safe

709
01:06:29.770 --> 01:06:33.700
This is my grandpa's old map.
It shows you where the loops are.

710
01:06:44.110 --> 01:06:51.250
That's him. thats the man I saw. Who is he?
Thats Barron. He is the Leader.

711
01:06:52.620 --> 01:06:59.830
Leader of what? Who are these people?
Bad people... bad peculiars.

712
01:07:01.070 --> 01:07:05.840
Abe dedicated his life to hunting them down.
These are the ones he never found

713
01:07:06.600 --> 01:07:09.210
What do you mean "hunting"?

714
01:07:11.480 --> 01:07:18.479
They raided homes. Whole homes full of children left for dead.
Abe took lives ...

715
01:07:18.480 --> 01:07:22.720
To save lifes.
He only retired when you were born to protect you.

716
01:07:23.320 --> 01:07:31.320
From what?
If I tell you the rest. you have to promise not to run away.

717
01:07:33.300 --> 01:07:41.300
Jake. you belong here.
You know that I dont. I'm not like you. I'm just ordinary

718
01:07:41.910 --> 01:07:47.840
Maybe not Jake. only a peculiar can enter a time loop.

719
01:07:50.280 --> 01:08:00.280
No. that can't be right. I mean... I would know.
Fine. Then I'll show you something else.

720
01:08:07.300 --> 01:08:08.630
Hurry! You'll miss it.

721
01:08:22.210 --> 01:08:25.949
Ymbrynes usually pick the perfect date to create a loop.
Now Ms. Peregrinee ..

722
01:08:25.950 --> 01:08:30.289
Had to do this in a rush.
Why?

723
01:08:30.290 --> 01:08:36.089
Because the Germans were about to drop a bomb on the house.
The point is. September the 3rd. 1943....

724
01:08:36.090 --> 01:08:41.530
wasn't perfect. The thing that killed Victor came back.

725
01:09:08.260 --> 01:09:11.160
Wait. watch out! ***********

726
01:09:39.490 --> 01:09:47.490
You can see it. can't you? No one else can. Its invisible. Jake.
That was Abe's greatest gift of all.

727
01:09:50.830 --> 01:09:53.240
He could see the monsters.

728
01:09:57.640 --> 01:10:02.149
We call them 'Holocaust'. Hollows. for short.

729
01:10:02.150 --> 01:10:08.049
My grandpa told me about people. who turn into monsters.
Is that what they are?

730
01:10:08.050 --> 01:10:14.019
I will explain everything. Jake. I fear its my duty now considering... but you should know that in doing so....

731
01:10:14.020 --> 01:10:21.060
I'm breaking a solemn promise.
I knew you were peculiar when you were born but your grandfather....

732
01:10:21.070 --> 01:10:26.199
forbid me to tell you anything.
His dearest wish was for you to have an ordinary childhood.

733
01:10:26.200 --> 01:10:31.739
Well I definitely had that.
He intended to tell you the truth when you turned 18.

734
01:10:31.740 --> 01:10:38.850
He hoped his bed-time stories would pave the way.
Here's my book.

735
01:10:50.960 --> 01:10:57.730
Many years ago. a splinter faction emerged among our people

736
01:10:57.740 --> 01:11:01.769
Disaffected peculiars tired of living in loops.
That's Mr. Barron.

737
01:11:01.770 --> 01:11:06.879
He believed that by harnessing the essence of an Ymbryne's powers.
he and his cronies

738
01:11:06.880 --> 01:11:13.780
Could gain immortality and be able to live outside loops.
He devised an experiment.

739
01:11:16.450 --> 01:11:21.790
He kidnapped an Ymbryne not knowing or caring
Whether she would survive the experiment

740
01:11:42.650 --> 01:11:47.280
But the fate of Barron and his group
was more horrifying still.

741
01:12:23.720 --> 01:12:26.320
Why didn't Barron turn into one?

742
01:12:39.140 --> 01:12:46.240
He did.
But years later he found a way to reverse the effects...
to regain humanity.

743
01:12:46.580 --> 01:12:50.568
They had become not immortal gods - but Hollows.

744
01:12:50.580 --> 01:12:54.580
invisible beasts. dangerous. cold-blooded. deadly!

745
01:12:54.890 --> 01:12:59.220
Remember I told you they raided loops? This is why

746
01:12:59.560 --> 01:13:06.300
Barron discovered that by consuming the eyes of other peculiars ... especially children.

747
01:13:13.340 --> 01:13:15.270
He began to change

748
01:13:33.120 --> 01:13:36.490
Consume enough. and a hollow can fully regain its human form

749
01:13:38.600 --> 01:13:41.060
Just as Barron and some of his friends did.

750
01:13:50.210 --> 01:13:57.479
The rest of them are stuck as Hollows.
Are you saying that Barron ate my uncle's ...

751
01:13:57.480 --> 01:14:03.590
He needs no more eyes himself. but I fear I led a Hollow to your grandfather. yes.

752
01:14:05.390 --> 01:14:11.190
After the first attacks on Loops. we all got better at hiding ...making new loops... keeping our

753
01:14:11.200 --> 01:14:16.899
Whereabouts secret.
The Hollows grow more desparate every year
and Barron wishes to help his friends

754
01:14:16.900 --> 01:14:21.040
Miss Peregrine! Come quickly! Miss Avocet's awake.

755
01:14:29.250 --> 01:14:35.489
Oh Miss Peregrine! They found my new loop. The children...
I tried to save them but there were so many Hollows...

756
01:14:35.490 --> 01:14:42.290
I dont know how I escaped.
You are safe now.

757
01:14:42.460 --> 01:14:46.160
None of us are safe. They set up the machine in my loop.

758
01:14:46.330 --> 01:14:50.629
They put in in the celler at Blackboat tower. They're still there...
The machine?

759
01:14:50.630 --> 01:14:56.509
The experiment. They intend to do it again! This time. he's using more Ymbrynes.

760
01:14:56.510 --> 01:14:58.880
He still wants to be immortal

761
01:15:02.150 --> 01:15:10.150
Do Hollows only attack peculiars?
Of course not! They're monsters. Jake.
they'll slaughter anything in their path.

762
01:15:10.550 --> 01:15:15.730
Well. some sheep on the island were killed.
You don't think they're here already. do you?

763
01:15:16.060 --> 01:15:24.060
Have you seen anyone with white eyes?
I'm sorry children. we can't remain here.

764
01:15:24.700 --> 01:15:28.200
What?
We leave on the first ferry. off the island tomorrow.

765
01:15:28.210 --> 01:15:31.770
Pack anything of importance.
I'll make sandwiches and lead you to bed

766
01:15:31.780 --> 01:15:34.479
Are we leaving for good? When are we coming back?

767
01:15:34.480 --> 01:15:37.309
Never. If Ms. Peregrine's not here to reset the loop
tomorrow night ...

768
01:15:37.310 --> 01:15:40.219
the house gets bombed. What? Our house?

769
01:15:40.220 --> 01:15:43.320
Dont cry. Miss Peregrine will find you another lovely house....
somewhere else

770
01:15:51.230 --> 01:15:55.260
Once this loop closes. that's it!
I can't get back to my own time

771
01:15:55.270 --> 01:16:00.699
You didn't seem very happy there. I can't just leave!
I have a family

